<br>
I shall endeavor to answer thine questions as best as I might, being a resident within Norrath these past 5+ (in game) years (*ooc* yikes... time flies... <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> )<br>
<br>
Thee need not the training of a language by thine guildmaster to begin to learn a language... thee need just find one who will be willing to chat with you for a time (*in group*).  Thee may learn a little bit of one langage, and only one language, each hour (* one point of any language per hour per zone *).  <br>
<br>
The one chatting unto thee (*teaching*) must be of a higher level in the language being spoken (1 point is sufficient) in order for thee to gain the Widsom of his or her teaching.  It is often requested that thee reciprocate by teaching thine friend a bit of thine language---or one thee've obtained that mayhap he or she has not.<br>
<br>
It does take time to learn such, and much commitment, howe'er, tis not an impossible thing to do.<br>
<br>
*ooc note* --- when you are first learning a language, you might see the &quot;your language skills have improved&quot; message, but looking at your skill list, might not see the new language.  If you zone, then recheck your skill list, you should note the new language in the list.<br>
<br>
Hope this helps <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> , and welcome unto Norrath and FV.<br>
